  "description": "A two-chamber and two-door inverter refrigerator of the 2024 model, presented on the market by the popular South Korean brand Samsung and positioned by the manufacturer in the upper price range. The model supports the ability to control and adjust operating modes remotely, using the SmartThings application. The total useful capacity of the device is 390 liters. The doors are compatible with BeSpoke decorative overlays. Cold circulation inside the working chambers is carried out according to the All Around Cooling system. This model uses an inverter compressor with a 20-year warranty. The cooling zone uses a metal Metal Cooling overlay, which accumulates cold for additional stabilization of the temperature regime. The Samsung BeSpoke RB38C7B5DB1 refrigerator received an Optimal Fresh + container with a dividing partition, as well as a separate drawer with the ability to adjust the humidity level. The door can be conveniently opened at 90 ° next to a solid wall on the side. The refrigerator has reduced operating noise - even when the high-performance cooling mode is turned on, the device produces noise no more than 35 dB. At the same time, the capacity of the device is quite sufficient to freeze up to 8 kg of products per day.",
